============================================================

Written the improvement plan. Here's the summary:

**Single failure**: `Faszerowana papryka` — returns `PAPRIKA GYERAN-JJIM` instead of the correct Polish title.

**Root cause**: The bilingual detection guard at line 392 requires `preAllCaps.length === 1` (exactly one ALL_CAPS candidate in the entire document). This document has 4 ALL_CAPS candidates (the Korean romanization + 3 section headers/serving info), so the guard never fires and the Korean romanization wins on bonus points (+0.18).

**Fix**: Replace the count-based guard with a **positional + semantic** check:
- Look for ALL_CAPS candidates at position 1–2 only (not globally)
- Validate via embedding cosine similarity (> 0.4) between the position-0 mixed-case candidate and the nearby ALL_CAPS candidate — confirming they're translations of the same dish
- Suppress only the confirmed translation, leaving all other ALL_CAPS candidates untouched

This requires zero new embedding calls (reuses existing rawScored embeddings), changes ~6 lines → ~15 lines in one block, and has low regression risk because the suppression scope is strictly narrower than before.
