{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017VcW5mg8g8GLn5Xde6iMaH","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I now have all the feedback and improvement plan files. Let me compile a comprehensive summary of the evolution of the title extractor.\n\n---\n\n## Title Extractor Evolution: Complete Summary\n\n### Iteration 1 (404c596) — Initial Analysis and Root Cause Diagnosis\n**Starting state:** 5 failed test cases out of 6 (83% failure rate)\n\n**Failures analyzed:**\n1. ARAYES SHRAK — extracted \"pepper + MAKES 8 ARAYES\" instead of full title\n2. Baked Eggs with Feta... — extracted with spurious \" + \" separator\n3. FINNISH MILK FLATBREADS + FINNISH POTATO FLATBREADS — extracted garbled \"DAT FLATBREADS\"\n4. OVERNIGHT STRAIGHT PIZZA DOUGH — extracted unrelated body text\n5. SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK... — extracted fragments \"ssekart + The + favoured by\"\n\n**Six common themes identified:**\n1. No recipe metadata filtering (SERVES, MAKES, BULK FERMENTATION lines treated as candidates)\n2. No OCR quality gate (garbled fragments pass all filters)\n3. Embedding scoring unreliably distinguishes titles from body text\n4. Position signal underweighted (only used as tiebreaker, not scoring factor)\n5. Multi-line title joining fragile (both parts compete equally in scoring)\n6. Output `+`-join format creates ambiguity between multi-part titles and multiple candidates\n\n---\n\n### Iteration 2 (072e8fb) — Proposed Five Changes, Focus on Scoring Signals\n**Plan:** Position-weighted scoring, metadata blocklist, OCR quality gate, ALL_CAPS bonus, stricter selection\n\n**Key changes proposed:**\n- Add position decay bonus (+0.15 at position 0, decaying to 0 after 50%)\n- Blocklist recipe metadata patterns (SERVES, MAKES, PREP TIME, etc.)\n- Enhanced garble detection with vowel ratios and lowercase-start checks\n- ALL_CAPS bonus (+0.08) as structural signal\n- Raise selection threshold from 60% to 80% of best score\n\n**Expected impact:** 4/5 failures fixed (83% → 100% projected)\n\n---\n\n### Iteration 3 (a5a0dca) — Inverted Dedup Logic and Multiplicative Position Scoring\n**New understanding:** The core dedup bug systematically removes complete multi-line titles in favor of partial first lines\n\n**Four major changes:**\n1. **Inverted substring dedup** — Remove shorter candidate when longer one contains it (was backwards)\n2. **Multiplicative position factor** — Position becomes a ×1.12 multiplier instead of +0.15 additive bonus (preventing weak early fragments from beating strong late titles)\n3. **Strengthened garble detection** — Multiple heuristics (remove 25-char limit, detect mid-text sentence boundaries, filter mixed-case garbled words)\n4. **First structural ALL_CAPS heading bonus** — Promote earliest ALL_CAPS multi-word candidate with ≥4 letters per word to +0.10 bonus\n\n**Critical insight:** Embedded in dedup and scoring was the fundamental insight that recipe titles have strong **structural signals** (position, ALL_CAPS, continuation punctuation) that often override embedding similarity.\n\n---\n\n### Iteration 4 (4ecc581) — Comprehensive Failure Root-Cause Analysis\n**New focus:** The dedup logic is fundamentally broken because it compares `rawScore` while bonuses (structural, ALL_CAPS) are applied separately\n\n**Three critical failures re-analyzed:**\n1. Baked Eggs: dedup removes the correct 2-line join because first-line fragment has equal rawScore\n2. Finnish Flatbreads (second title missing): `structuralBonus` of +0.10 on first title inflates `bestBaseScore`, raising threshold beyond second title's reach\n3. Saffron Wheat Buns: OCR corruption (FRON ← SAFFRON) claims firstStructuralHeading role, kills correct join via dedup\n\n**Proposed fixes:**\n1. Use final `score` (with bonuses) in dedup, prefer longer on ties\n2. Continuation-aware firstStructuralHeading (strip `/&+:()` tokens before checking word lengths)\n3. Compute threshold from position-free `baseScore` (exclude position factor inflation)\n\n---\n\n### Iteration 5 (218113e) — Origin Tracking and Continuation Join Protection\n**Realization:** The dedup mechanism needs metadata to distinguish legitimate joins from noise\n\n**Five changes:**\n1. Track `origin` field (\"single\", \"2-line\", \"3-line\") on candidates\n2. Protect continuation joins by removing single-line prefix when the join survived (only for continuation-char joins)\n3. Distribute structuralBonus to ALL structural headings (+0.06 base + +0.04 first-heading tiebreaker = +0.10 total)\n4. Select baseHeading by embedding quality (rawScore), not position\n5. OCR truncation cross-validation (penalty if word appears as suffix of another heading's word)\n\n---\n\n### Iteration 6 (8a6c985) — Restructured Scoring into Two Passes\n**Major restructuring:** Split embedding scoring into two passes to enable embedding-quality baseHeading selection before bonuses\n\n**Changes implemented:**\n1. Restructured scoring: compute `rawScore` first (all embeddings), select baseHeading, then apply bonuses in second pass\n2. Added `thresholdScore` field that excludes structural bonus from threshold computation (fixes multi-title suppression bug)\n3. Refined continuation-aware structural heading check\n4. Hard disqualification (-0.15 → -1.0) for truncated OCR words\n\n---\n\n### Iteration 7 (9a83c46) — Suffix Fragment Removal and Evaluation Harness Awareness\n**New discoveries:** Continuation protection was one-directional (prefix only), and some failures are evaluation harness bugs\n\n**Results:** 6/8 passing (75%)\n\n**Remaining failures:**\n1. Baked Eggs — suffix fragment \"& Coriander\" survives and kills join via dedup\n2. Saffron Wheat Buns — OCR character mismatch (`:` in expected, `/` in OCR text)\n\n**Changes proposed:**\n1. Extend suffix fragment removal (not just prefix)\n2. Normalize `/` ↔ `:` in evaluation harness\n\n---\n\n### Iteration 8 (b5177f1) — Structural Signals Over Embeddings + Bilingual Title Protection\n**Major philosophical shift:** Recognize that structural signals (position 0, continuation punctuation, ALL_CAPS) are often MORE reliable than embeddings\n\n**Four comprehensive changes:**\n1. **Pre-merge continuation lines** — Move merging upstream before candidate generation, preventing continuation chars from ever becoming standalone candidates\n2. **Ingredient-gap detection** — Distinguish section headers from recipe titles by checking if ALL_CAPS candidates are followed by ingredient lines (measurements, numbers)\n3. **First-line mixed-case protection** — Prefer position-0 mixed-case candidate over position-1 ALL_CAPS subtitle (bilingual cookbooks)\n4. **Evaluation harness separator normalization** (trivial fix)\n\n**Status:** 4/8 passing before iteration 8 implementation\n\n---\n\n### Iteration 9 (Current) — Pre-Threshold Bilingual Detection and Empty-Pool Fallback\n**Results:** 6/8 passing (75%)\n\n**Two targeted failures:**\n1. Baked Eggs — embedding threshold discards sole candidate because ingredient words inflate `headerSim`\n2. Faszerowana papryka — ALL_CAPS bonuses inflate threshold, preventing first-line mixed-case title from being considered\n\n**Two complementary fixes:**\n1. **Pre-threshold bilingual detection** — Move detection before threshold filtering so ALL_CAPS bonuses don't prevent correct title from reaching `selected`\n2. **Empty-pool fallback** — When all candidates fail threshold, return best positional candidate as safety net (all passed hard filters)\n\n**Key insight:** The threshold gate has absolute veto power with no fallback. Hard filters are structural validators, but embeddings can be unreliable for ingredient-heavy recipes.\n\n---\n\n## Common Threads Across All Iterations\n\n### The Dedup Problem (Iterations 1-7)\nThe \"shorter wins on substring\" rule was designed for `\"Pierogi Ruskie 200g mąki...\"` → keep `\"Pierogi Ruskie\"`, but systematically destroyed split titles like `\"ARAYES\" + \"SHRAK\"` → `\"ARAYES SHRAK\"` where both parts independently pass filters.\n\n**Evolution:** Fixed in iteration 3 (invert logic), solidified in iteration 4 (use final score not rawScore), but edge cases persisted until iteration 8 (pre-merge upstream).\n\n### The Threshold Leakage Problem (Iterations 3-6)\nBonuses on one candidate inflated the threshold via `bestScore`, unfairly excluding equally-valid subsequent candidates.\n\n**Evolution:** Recognized in iteration 4, attempted in iteration 4 (position-free baseScore), fully implemented in iteration 6 (thresholdScore field), but remaining issues around bilingual pages solved in iteration 9 (pre-threshold detection).\n\n### Embedding Limitations (Iterations 1, 8-9)\nPure embedding similarity cannot distinguish \"dish named after ingredients\" from \"ingredient list fragment.\"\n\n**Evolution:** Initially attempted to fix with bonuses (iteration 2), realized structural signals are actually stronger (iteration 8), finally added safety net fallback when embeddings fail (iteration 9).\n\n### Structural Signal Underutilization (Iterations 1-8)\nPosition, ALL_CAPS, continuation characters, and document structure are strong signals but were treated as minor bonuses rather than decision gates.\n\n**Evolution:** Grew from position bonus (iteration 2) → multiplicative position factor (iteration 3) → structural heading bonus (iteration 3) → pre-merge continuation logic (iteration 8) → pre-threshold bilingual detection (iteration 9).\n\n---\n\n## Current Status\n\n**Iteration 9 projected:** 8/8 = 100% accuracy (with both remaining fixes implemented)\n\nThe journey reveals a pattern: **each iteration added layers of structural understanding** that moved the algorithm from \"pure embeddings with tuning knobs\" toward \"embeddings as one signal among many structural validators.\" The most effective fixes came when the algorithm started treating hard filters and position as binding constraints rather than scoring decorations."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a6ede27a8de5a6137 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 124562\ntool_uses: 17\nduration_ms: 40638</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"688165a7-dc9e-4c33-9dca-71554537d527","uuid":"0d7872ad-33e0-427a-92d3-a2c13c0741e5","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read all the feedback.md files in these directories and summarize each one concisely (what failed, why, and what fix was applied):\n\n- tools/title-loop/docs/1-404c596/feedback.md\n- tools/title-loop/docs/2-072e8fb/feedback.md\n- tools/title-loop/docs/3-a5a0dca/feedback.md\n- tools/title-loop/docs/4-4ecc581/feedback.md\n- tools/title-loop/docs/5-218113e/feedback.md\n- tools/title-loop/docs/6-8a6c985/feedback.md\n- tools/title-loop/docs/7-9a83c46/feedback.md\n- tools/title-loop/docs/8-b5177f1/feedback.md\n\nAlso check if there are improvement-plan.md files in any of these directories and read them too. Give me a comprehensive summary of the evolution of the title extractor.","agentId":"a6ede27a8de5a6137","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I now have all the feedback and improvement plan files. Let me compile a comprehensive summary of the evolution of the title extractor.\n\n---\n\n## Title Extractor Evolution: Complete Summary\n\n### Iteration 1 (404c596) — Initial Analysis and Root Cause Diagnosis\n**Starting state:** 5 failed test cases out of 6 (83% failure rate)\n\n**Failures analyzed:**\n1. ARAYES SHRAK — extracted \"pepper + MAKES 8 ARAYES\" instead of full title\n2. Baked Eggs with Feta... — extracted with spurious \" + \" separator\n3. FINNISH MILK FLATBREADS + FINNISH POTATO FLATBREADS — extracted garbled \"DAT FLATBREADS\"\n4. OVERNIGHT STRAIGHT PIZZA DOUGH — extracted unrelated body text\n5. SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK... — extracted fragments \"ssekart + The + favoured by\"\n\n**Six common themes identified:**\n1. No recipe metadata filtering (SERVES, MAKES, BULK FERMENTATION lines treated as candidates)\n2. No OCR quality gate (garbled fragments pass all filters)\n3. Embedding scoring unreliably distinguishes titles from body text\n4. Position signal underweighted (only used as tiebreaker, not scoring factor)\n5. Multi-line title joining fragile (both parts compete equally in scoring)\n6. Output `+`-join format creates ambiguity between multi-part titles and multiple candidates\n\n---\n\n### Iteration 2 (072e8fb) — Proposed Five Changes, Focus on Scoring Signals\n**Plan:** Position-weighted scoring, metadata blocklist, OCR quality gate, ALL_CAPS bonus, stricter selection\n\n**Key changes proposed:**\n- Add position decay bonus (+0.15 at position 0, decaying to 0 after 50%)\n- Blocklist recipe metadata patterns (SERVES, MAKES, PREP TIME, etc.)\n- Enhanced garble detection with vowel ratios and lowercase-start checks\n- ALL_CAPS bonus (+0.08) as structural signal\n- Raise selection threshold from 60% to 80% of best score\n\n**Expected impact:** 4/5 failures fixed (83% → 100% projected)\n\n---\n\n### Iteration 3 (a5a0dca) — Inverted Dedup Logic and Multiplicative Position Scoring\n**New understanding:** The core dedup bug systematically removes complete multi-line titles in favor of partial first lines\n\n**Four major changes:**\n1. **Inverted substring dedup** — Remove shorter candidate when longer one contains it (was backwards)\n2. **Multiplicative position factor** — Position becomes a ×1.12 multiplier instead of +0.15 additive bonus (preventing weak early fragments from beating strong late titles)\n3. **Strengthened garble detection** — Multiple heuristics (remove 25-char limit, detect mid-text sentence boundaries, filter mixed-case garbled words)\n4. **First structural ALL_CAPS heading bonus** — Promote earliest ALL_CAPS multi-word candidate with ≥4 letters per word to +0.10 bonus\n\n**Critical insight:** Embedded in dedup and scoring was the fundamental insight that recipe titles have strong **structural signals** (position, ALL_CAPS, continuation punctuation) that often override embedding similarity.\n\n---\n\n### Iteration 4 (4ecc581) — Comprehensive Failure Root-Cause Analysis\n**New focus:** The dedup logic is fundamentally broken because it compares `rawScore` while bonuses (structural, ALL_CAPS) are applied separately\n\n**Three critical failures re-analyzed:**\n1. Baked Eggs: dedup removes the correct 2-line join because first-line fragment has equal rawScore\n2. Finnish Flatbreads (second title missing): `structuralBonus` of +0.10 on first title inflates `bestBaseScore`, raising threshold beyond second title's reach\n3. Saffron Wheat Buns: OCR corruption (FRON ← SAFFRON) claims firstStructuralHeading role, kills correct join via dedup\n\n**Proposed fixes:**\n1. Use final `score` (with bonuses) in dedup, prefer longer on ties\n2. Continuation-aware firstStructuralHeading (strip `/&+:()` tokens before checking word lengths)\n3. Compute threshold from position-free `baseScore` (exclude position factor inflation)\n\n---\n\n### Iteration 5 (218113e) — Origin Tracking and Continuation Join Protection\n**Realization:** The dedup mechanism needs metadata to distinguish legitimate joins from noise\n\n**Five changes:**\n1. Track `origin` field (\"single\", \"2-line\", \"3-line\") on candidates\n2. Protect continuation joins by removing single-line prefix when the join survived (only for continuation-char joins)\n3. Distribute structuralBonus to ALL structural headings (+0.06 base + +0.04 first-heading tiebreaker = +0.10 total)\n4. Select baseHeading by embedding quality (rawScore), not position\n5. OCR truncation cross-validation (penalty if word appears as suffix of another heading's word)\n\n---\n\n### Iteration 6 (8a6c985) — Restructured Scoring into Two Passes\n**Major restructuring:** Split embedding scoring into two passes to enable embedding-quality baseHeading selection before bonuses\n\n**Changes implemented:**\n1. Restructured scoring: compute `rawScore` first (all embeddings), select baseHeading, then apply bonuses in second pass\n2. Added `thresholdScore` field that excludes structural bonus from threshold computation (fixes multi-title suppression bug)\n3. Refined continuation-aware structural heading check\n4. Hard disqualification (-0.15 → -1.0) for truncated OCR words\n\n---\n\n### Iteration 7 (9a83c46) — Suffix Fragment Removal and Evaluation Harness Awareness\n**New discoveries:** Continuation protection was one-directional (prefix only), and some failures are evaluation harness bugs\n\n**Results:** 6/8 passing (75%)\n\n**Remaining failures:**\n1. Baked Eggs — suffix fragment \"& Coriander\" survives and kills join via dedup\n2. Saffron Wheat Buns — OCR character mismatch (`:` in expected, `/` in OCR text)\n\n**Changes proposed:**\n1. Extend suffix fragment removal (not just prefix)\n2. Normalize `/` ↔ `:` in evaluation harness\n\n---\n\n### Iteration 8 (b5177f1) — Structural Signals Over Embeddings + Bilingual Title Protection\n**Major philosophical shift:** Recognize that structural signals (position 0, continuation punctuation, ALL_CAPS) are often MORE reliable than embeddings\n\n**Four comprehensive changes:**\n1. **Pre-merge continuation lines** — Move merging upstream before candidate generation, preventing continuation chars from ever becoming standalone candidates\n2. **Ingredient-gap detection** — Distinguish section headers from recipe titles by checking if ALL_CAPS candidates are followed by ingredient lines (measurements, numbers)\n3. **First-line mixed-case protection** — Prefer position-0 mixed-case candidate over position-1 ALL_CAPS subtitle (bilingual cookbooks)\n4. **Evaluation harness separator normalization** (trivial fix)\n\n**Status:** 4/8 passing before iteration 8 implementation\n\n---\n\n### Iteration 9 (Current) — Pre-Threshold Bilingual Detection and Empty-Pool Fallback\n**Results:** 6/8 passing (75%)\n\n**Two targeted failures:**\n1. Baked Eggs — embedding threshold discards sole candidate because ingredient words inflate `headerSim`\n2. Faszerowana papryka — ALL_CAPS bonuses inflate threshold, preventing first-line mixed-case title from being considered\n\n**Two complementary fixes:**\n1. **Pre-threshold bilingual detection** — Move detection before threshold filtering so ALL_CAPS bonuses don't prevent correct title from reaching `selected`\n2. **Empty-pool fallback** — When all candidates fail threshold, return best positional candidate as safety net (all passed hard filters)\n\n**Key insight:** The threshold gate has absolute veto power with no fallback. Hard filters are structural validators, but embeddings can be unreliable for ingredient-heavy recipes.\n\n---\n\n## Common Threads Across All Iterations\n\n### The Dedup Problem (Iterations 1-7)\nThe \"shorter wins on substring\" rule was designed for `\"Pierogi Ruskie 200g mąki...\"` → keep `\"Pierogi Ruskie\"`, but systematically destroyed split titles like `\"ARAYES\" + \"SHRAK\"` → `\"ARAYES SHRAK\"` where both parts independently pass filters.\n\n**Evolution:** Fixed in iteration 3 (invert logic), solidified in iteration 4 (use final score not rawScore), but edge cases persisted until iteration 8 (pre-merge upstream).\n\n### The Threshold Leakage Problem (Iterations 3-6)\nBonuses on one candidate inflated the threshold via `bestScore`, unfairly excluding equally-valid subsequent candidates.\n\n**Evolution:** Recognized in iteration 4, attempted in iteration 4 (position-free baseScore), fully implemented in iteration 6 (thresholdScore field), but remaining issues around bilingual pages solved in iteration 9 (pre-threshold detection).\n\n### Embedding Limitations (Iterations 1, 8-9)\nPure embedding similarity cannot distinguish \"dish named after ingredients\" from \"ingredient list fragment.\"\n\n**Evolution:** Initially attempted to fix with bonuses (iteration 2), realized structural signals are actually stronger (iteration 8), finally added safety net fallback when embeddings fail (iteration 9).\n\n### Structural Signal Underutilization (Iterations 1-8)\nPosition, ALL_CAPS, continuation characters, and document structure are strong signals but were treated as minor bonuses rather than decision gates.\n\n**Evolution:** Grew from position bonus (iteration 2) → multiplicative position factor (iteration 3) → structural heading bonus (iteration 3) → pre-merge continuation logic (iteration 8) → pre-threshold bilingual detection (iteration 9).\n\n---\n\n## Current Status\n\n**Iteration 9 projected:** 8/8 = 100% accuracy (with both remaining fixes implemented)\n\nThe journey reveals a pattern: **each iteration added layers of structural understanding** that moved the algorithm from \"pure embeddings with tuning knobs\" toward \"embeddings as one signal among many structural validators.\" The most effective fixes came when the algorithm started treating hard filters and position as binding constraints rather than scoring decorations."}],"totalDurationMs":40638,"totalTokens":124562,"totalToolUseCount":17,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":42230,"cache_read_input_tokens":79858,"output_tokens":2467,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":42230},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
